  "text": "We analysed parental age effects on offspring telomere length in mixed models with normally distributed errors. These models included nested random effects of parental and brood identity to account for the non-independence of offspring from the same parent (within and between years) and brood, and a linear covariate for parental age. Because transgenerational senescence effects were found to be sex-specific [CITATION_1] , we additionally fitted a two-level class variable for offspring sex (with males as the reference category) and the interaction between offspring sex and parental age.",
